reviews.text: This is was the best stuffed crust that I have ever tried! There's not so much choice for vegetarian pizza here, but I found my stuff and we shared a pizza with my husband drinking their craft beer on tap. It was very satisfying. Of course we could not finish it all in the restaurant üòÜThe only thing: the stuffing of pizza was so juicy that it melted away the crust in the middle.

Decided to stop for lunch after a weekend at the lake. Establishment is clean, open and can tell the owners took pride in remodeling what looks like an old gas station/repair shop.

Waitress was spectacular. Complimentary breadsticks were delicious.

Great staff, great food, great place!

The food is delicious. Cozy, but spacious seating! Staff are friendly and attentive.

We got the Frisco sub, Nashville sub, a dessert pizza and we had family do a food challenge of pizza and wings. They didn't succeed in eating it all by the timer, but they tried!

Well worth the hour drive for us. We ordered a small cheese pizza with original crust and a large supreme Chicago-style style pizza. Both were absolutely delicious. No complaints. Quick service and very clean.

A great place to enjoy a good pizza in Murphysboro, IL. I went during  lunch time in a weekday and ordered a small Hawaiian Volcano pizza with a regular soda. The place is nice and new and everything was clean. The staff was kind and I waited 10 minutes for the pizza, an acceptable time for me. The small size is enough for a person, the taste was good and the quantity of cheese, ham, pineapple. Jalapenos and the other ingredients, was ok. They provided the pizza in a box, ready to go, but there are plastic plates, forks and knives that you can take to eat inside. In conclusion, I recommend this place to all the pizza lovers.

detailedReviews.author: Andrew Snyder
detailedReviews.text: Order 1 lg cheese pizza, 1 lg pepperoni pizza and a cheese sticks. Placed my order at 640pm and got my pizza at 833pm on 10/23 spending $56.00. Called them twice and was told "Sorry we have one driver, it will be a bit longer" the food was not warm by any means. Our last 3 visits we have noticed that the Murphy location has gone down hill as to customer service and food quality. Waiting almost 2 hrs management needs to find a way to retain customers.

detailedReviews.author: Kimberly Rodriguez
detailedReviews.text: We ordered delivery, so I can not comment on the atmosphere of the restaurant. We ordered online, but the service was friendly upon delivery which was quick, less than 30 minutes. The two pizza were fresh out of the oven hot üî•. Lots of cheese and toppings on both the pepperoni and meat lovers pizzas. This was our first time having Martel's Pizza. We will definitely eat here again when in town.

detailedReviews.author: Sandra Underwood
detailedReviews.text: The pizza was fast food quality. We called to have it ready when we arrived. Seemed they put it in after we got there, even though I explained that we were picking up on the way to a destination. Had to ask for things to take a long, even though at other Martels, they were handed to you with your pizza. The girl had to go and hunt them down. More time lost for us. Probably will they a different place next time.

detailedReviews.author: Jamie Wadington
detailedReviews.text: I have been a local for several years. I love the pizza and the staff are great. My problem is the prices. They have no good deals, in my opinion. I think $37 for 2 large 1 topping pizzas is way overpriced. Because of this, I will be getting my pizza elsewhere from now on.

detailedReviews.author: Joshua Freytag
detailedReviews.text: Stopped in around 1 pm for some pizza by the slice and got 2 slices and a sweet tea for $5!!!! The taco pizza stomps all over Casey's taco pizza and the sweet tea was amazing!!!!! Oh and don't let me forget about the service which also very friendly. I will definitely be coming back in the future!! Keep up the great work guys you just got yourselves a regular customer.

detailedReviews.author: Katlin Kirby
detailedReviews.text: I have never had an order correct or on time without needing a full refund.

detailedReviews.author: Jonathan Dror

detailedReviews.author: Victoria Thomas
detailedReviews.text: Great pizza place. Lunch special every day from 11-2 for $5. 2 slices of pizza with  drink. Great deal. Can't wait to come back

detailedReviews.author: Allegra Wentworth
detailedReviews.text:
Giving 5 stars because honestly the pizza was very good and it being our first time having Martel's, it's exciting to know we have another pizza place to choose from!

However! I do warn ordering online, especially if you order on the weekend and/or order a large Chicago style pizza.

Although quick and efficient, their automatic online time estimate is about 30 minutes, which may be a bit generous for the large Chicago pizza. I'd say give that at least 45 min before heading over! Waiting on good pizza is something I'm going to continue to regardless and so won't keep us from returning BUT it wasn't super fun standing around for nearly another 30 minutes ...especially after being told it would only be a couple minutes when we walked in, lol.

P.s. We got light cheese and extra sauce on the Chicago, and it was great. Also, the staff at the counter were very polite and apologetic.

detailedReviews.author: Doug B
detailedReviews.text: Great deals and food is even better!!!!
